      • setSwipeThreshold

        public void setSwipeThreshold(float swipeThreshold)
        Set the fraction that the user should move the View to be considered as swiped. The fraction is calculated with respect to RecyclerView's bounds.

        Default value is .5f, which means, to swipe a View, user must move the View at least half of RecyclerView's width or height, depending on the swipe direction.

        参数:
        swipeThreshold - A float value that denotes the fraction of the View size. Default value is .8f .

      • setMoveThreshold

        public void setMoveThreshold(float moveThreshold)
        Set the fraction that the user should move the View to be considered as it is dragged. After a view is moved this amount, ItemTouchHelper starts checking for Views below it for a possible drop.
        参数:
        moveThreshold - A float value that denotes the fraction of the View size. Default value is .1f .

      • setDragMoveFlags

        public void setDragMoveFlags(int dragMoveFlags)

        Set the drag movement direction.

        The value should be ItemTouchHelper.UP, ItemTouchHelper.DOWN, ItemTouchHelper.LEFT, ItemTouchHelper.RIGHT or their combination.

        You can combine them like ItemTouchHelper.UP | ItemTouchHelper.DOWN, it means that the item could only move up and down when dragged.
        参数:
        dragMoveFlags - the drag movement direction. Default value is ItemTouchHelper.UP | ItemTouchHelper.DOWN | ItemTouchHelper.LEFT | ItemTouchHelper.RIGHT.

      • setSwipeMoveFlags

        public void setSwipeMoveFlags(int swipeMoveFlags)

        Set the swipe movement direction.

        The value should be ItemTouchHelper.START, ItemTouchHelper.END or their combination.

        You can combine them like ItemTouchHelper.START | ItemTouchHelper.END, it means that the item could swipe to both left or right.
        参数:
        swipeMoveFlags - the swipe movement direction. Default value is ItemTouchHelper.END.
